ities and the complex gender politics that are mass-produced when these efforts are commercialized.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican American women in literature. 0aAfrican American womenxIntellectual life. 0aAfrican American womenxPsychology. 0aAmerican literaturexAfrican American authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican literaturexWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aHealing. 0aPsychic trauma in literature. 0aPsychological literaturezUnited States. 0aSelf-help techniqueszUnited States. 0aSpiritual life in literature. 4aAfrican American Studies : African American Studies. 4aCommunication : Communication. 4aEducation : Education. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846244840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438462448423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438462448/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles